==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rechabite
<hw>Re"chab*ite</hw> <pr>(r⟦emac⟧"k⟦acr⟧b*⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Jewish Hist.)</fld> <def>One of the descendants of Jonadab, the
son of Rechab, all of whom by his injunction abstained from the use of
intoxicating drinks and even from planting the vine. <xex>Jer</xex>.
<xex>xxxv</xex>. 2-19. Also, in modern times, a member of a certain
society of abstainers from alcoholic liquors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

